## Overview

This document serves as an index to the individual Product Requirement Documents (PRDs) for the Lightspeed Wholesale storefront app. The app has been split into four focused feature PRDs to support independent development, modularization, and potential extraction into separate Ecwid apps.

---

## Feature PRDs

### 1. Wholesale Registration
**File:** [registration.prd](./registration.prd)

**Summary:** Account-based wholesale registration + edit flow integrated into Ecwid's `/products/account/register` (non-wholesale) and `/products/account/edit` (wholesale) pages. Prefills customer data from storefront, submits to external **Registration Server** using session token authentication. Server handles all Admin REST operations (profile updates, extra fields persistence, immediate group assignment).

**Current Status:** âœ… Complete â€” External server architecture with full persistence

**Architecture:** Client-Server
- **Client:** Form rendering, validation, session token auth
- **Server:** Admin REST operations, group assignment, idempotency

**Key Features:**
- Custom registration form injection on account pages (register for non-wholesale, edit for wholesale)
- Access rules: guests redirected to `/account`; non-wholesale blocked from edit; wholesale blocked from register
- Mode-specific UX: email shown read-only in register, hidden in edit; button text Register vs Save; success banners differ and edit redirects to `/products/account`
- Prefill from `Ecwid.Customer.get()` and extra field UI metadata from `Ecwid.getAppPublicConfig(clientId)["extraFields"]`
- Submit to external Registration Server at `REG_SERVER_URL/api/register` with session token (Bearer) + `Idempotency-Key`
- Server handles: profile updates, extra fields, group assignment
- Persistent success/error banners (5s, survives navigation); one-time auto-redirect for non-wholesale users to registration
- Account info card renders on `/products/account` with customer name/state/email
- Telemetry tracking

